  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (3497cdc 2022-05-08T00:04:18.132850+00:00)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge verify-contract\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\n`forge verify-contract` should allow for verifying files which outside of `src/` e.g. contracts which are imported as libs - by updating the following conditional statement: https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/2b1bc1e6941ad0593c2c1291eb10f36ab5f94bae/cli/src/cmd/forge/verify.rs#L151\r\n",
